Dear Firas Bawazir,

Thank you for your information. Based on your situation, you obtained 
your *KTP, KK, and NPWP* in 2023.

Your main source of income currently comes from the properties 
registered under your name.

In Indonesia, income from renting out a house through *Airbnb* falls 
under the category of *rental income from property*, which is generally 
subject to *Final Income Tax (PPh Final)* at a *rate of 10%*.

Regarding tax payments, you are required to *pay monthly* if you receive 
rental income on a monthly basis. However, if there is no rental income 
in a given month, you are *not required* to submit or pay the tax for 
that period. At the end of the fiscal year, you will only need to file 
your *annual personal tax return*, as the tax has already been paid monthly.

If you need further clarification, we can arrange an *online 
consultation*. Our fee for a *1-hour consultation* is *IDR 3.6 million*.

Please let us know if you would like to proceed.

Thank you for your cooperation.

*Best regards,*

